news.title: Lucknow divisional commissioner warns EESL to repair all street lights or face FIR
news.para: At a meeting to review the status street lights in the city, Jacob reprimanded officers of the LMC and the PSU. She said all the street lights of the city should either be changed or repaired within a week.

news.title: Dubai's Union Properties agrees to $162 million debt restructuring plan
news.para: The restructuring plan includes the repayment of 223 million dirhams to lenders and is expected to reduce financing costs and improve the company's cash flow generation, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Panel holds owner & contractor responsible for building collapse in Gurugram
news.para: The committee formed by the district administration submitted its report to Gurugram's deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav on Monday.

news.title: Chhattisgarh housing board to cut water supply of tax defaulters, colonies
news.para: Most housing board residents have not been regular in paying water tax, common maintenance tax, land maintenance charge, among others, leading to financial crisis in the housing board.

news.title: Over 4.5 lakh families to get new houses in Madhya Pradesh on Oct 22
news.para: "Under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana, 4.50 lakh beneficiaries in the state will get their own houses on the occasion of Diwali. Prime Minister Narendra Modi will conduct their 'grih pravesh' virtually," the chief minister said.

news.title: Visakhapatnam commissioner directs officials to prepare plans to distribute TIDCO houses
news.para: Raja Babu asked the officials to prepare a list of those who have already submitted demand drafts but later deemed ineligible for TIDCO housing, to hand over the DDs back to them.

news.title: Godrej creating unnecessary hurdles in land acquisition for bullet train: Maharashtra govt
news.para: ​A division bench of Justices Nitin Jamdar and Sharmila Deshmukh was hearing a petition filed by Godrej & Boyce Manufacturing Co Ltd challenging an order of September 15, 2022 passed by the state government awarding compensation to it for land acquisition for the project.

news.title: Defaulters face music, Nashik civic body collects Rs 75 lakh property tax
news.para: NMC officials said drums were played in front of the houses of 73 tax defaulters. Around 40 of the tax defaulters paid their tax dues amounting to Rs 74 crore to the civic body on the first

news.title: Ambuja Cements allots 47.74 crore warrants to Adani family firm; raises Rs  5,000 crore
news.para: As per the terms and conditions, the Adani group family has contributed Rs 5,000.15 crore, which is "25 per cent of the Limited issued price", it added.

news.title: Kolkata: KMRC to redevelop 26 houses razed in Bowbazar cave-in zone
news.para: ​While 23 houses were pulled down after the first subsidence on August 31, 2019, three more houses were demolished after irreparable cracks developed in the subsidence in May this year.

news.title: Revival charges needed to restore cancelled Chandigarh housing board dwelling unit licences
news.para: In case allotment of a dwelling unit is cancelled due to non-payment of license fee, revival charges shall be calculated at 10% of the accumulated outstanding amount of license fee.

news.title: Shimla draft development plan 2041 illegal, at odds with earlier orders: NGT
news.para: The plan was made in February but now it can’t be brought into effect and it also can’t validate any action that violates the NGT’s judgment.

news.title: Indore civic body starts verifying building permission documents
news.para: As per civic body officials, an 80ft road has been planned by the civic body on this stretch with an aim to solve traffic jams and congestion problems.

news.title: Urban estate to come up on 2,000 acres in Ludhiana: Punjab housing minister
news.para: Glada is already in the process of acquiring around 2,000-acre site at Ladowal bypass in Bagga Kalan, Noorpur Bet, Garha and Gounspur villages.

news.title: Reduce tax on commercial properties: CREDAI Nashik
news.para: The business of renting out commercial properties has been adversely affected in Nashik due to Covid-19 and the higher property tax rates that came into force from the 2018-19 fiscal.
